title: 664-A
statement: A. Complicated GCDtime limit per test1 secondmemory limit per test256 megabytesinputstandard inputoutputstandard outputGreatest common divisorGCD(a,b)of two positive integersaandbis equal to the biggest integerdsuch that both integersaandbare divisible byd. There are many efficient algorithms to find greatest common divisorGCD(a,b), for example, Euclid algorithm.Formally, find the biggest integerd, such that all integersa,a+ 1,a+ 2, ...,bare divisible byd.
